0World%20users%20in%20Argentina.%20The%20app%20does%20not%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erely%20on%20credit%20scores%2C%20collateral%2C%20or%20income%20verification%20to%20give%20people%20loans%2C%20which%20start%20as%20low%20as%20%245%2C%20and%20are%20capped%20at%20%24100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20they%20repay%2C%20they%20get%20to%20access%20increasingly%20larger%20loans%2C%26quot%3B%20Estevez%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3B%E2%80%8AThe%20progression%20of%20loans%20is%20structured%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20you%20cannot%20repay%20a%20small%20loan%20to%20then%20default%20on%20a%20greater%20loan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20essence%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20to%20game%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEstevez's%20system%20to%20earn%20quick%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEstevez%20said%20that%20close%20to%20100%2C000%20users%20have%20downloaded%20and%20opened%20the%20app%20since%20it%20launched%20and%2015%2C000%20loans%20have%20been%20issued.%20While%20Credit%20is%20anonymous%20and%20doesn't%20track%20how%20users%20spend%20the%20money%2C%20Estevez%20believes%20they're%20using%20it%20for%20everyday%20necessities%20like%20groceries%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20medicine.%20He%20said%20he%20knows%20users%20have%20become%20dependent%20on%20it%20given%20the%20onslaught%20of%20messages%20he%20receives%20whenever%20the%20app%20goes%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sudden%20success%20of%20Credit%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20realities%20of%20the%20developing%20world%20where%20many%20people%20have%20access%20to%20the%20internet%20and%20phone%2C%20but%20no%20meaningful%20way%20to%20obtain%20credit.%20It%20may%20also%20reveal%20what%20drives%20an%20app%20ecosystem%20built%20on%20human%20necessity%20rather%20than%20profit%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-see-your-apple-app-store-purchase-history-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple's%20App%20Store%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorld%20aims%20to%20grow%20its%20network%20through%